PPG Industries Inc will continue toshow earnings growth in 1987 despite a difficult economicclimate, the company said in its annual report, mailed toshareholders today.    For 1986, the company's earnings rose five pct, to 316 mlndlrs, on revenues that increased eight pct, to 4.7 billiondlrs. Earnings per share were 2.66 dlrs, compared with 2.27dlrs.    The company added that in 1986 its return on equity reached17.3 pct, up from 15.5 pct in 1985 and close to its goal of 18pct. Reuter&#3;